   "source": [
    "# Preparing the data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 74,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x=data.iloc[:,:-1].values\n",
    "y=data.iloc[:,1].values"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Train Test Spilt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 75,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#now the next step is to spikt this data into training and teat sets\n",
    "#we will do this by using scikrit-Learn's built- in train_test_split()method:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 78,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "x_train,x_test,y_train,y_test=train_test_split(x,y,\n",
    "                                               test_size=0.2,random_state=0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 79,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "LinearRegression()"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 79,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "reg=LinearRegression()\n",
    "reg.fit(x_train,y_train)"
   ]
